			<div class="content" id="post-content-2418374">
									

<p>As the saying goes, dragons make things cool.</p>
<p>I give especial love to the final poem (a bit of bias since I am one of the so-called &quot;descendants of the dragon&quot;). It is interesting to compare the Sarkic God and MEKHANE with Nüwa and Fuxi respectively, a lovely exercise in comparative mythology (that goes beyond the Mediterranean myths that the CotBG/Sarkic conflict seems to be centred on).</p>
<p>So Yaldabaoth is in Jupiter&#8230;</p>

