								<div class="title" id="post-title-2418898">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sunnyclockwork" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1621343); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1621343&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610205196" alt="SunnyClockwork" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1621343)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sunnyclockwork" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1621343); return false;" >SunnyClockwork</a></span> <span class="odate time_1449509795 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">07 Dec 2015 17:36</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2418898">
									

<p>In regarding to Chinese name, I'd say 龙宗 may sound better :P</p>
<p>Altho to be clear, this faction of CotBG Foundation discovered is not the same as the serpent people, whose empire died out thousands of years ago. This faction is more of a newly formed small group of people, like honesty, I imagine five or six people, who based their beliefs on some ancient texts, and various other information they found, and some of them may not even agree on the dragon part. The part they agree most on would be human is bascially created by the union of the two gods.</p>
<p>Altho the general dragon-worship part of the religion throughtout the history is probably influenced by the serpent people after all, being that they're one of the earliest. And the serpent people probably won't have a name for their beliefs, being that they also worship other gods, just that the dragons are the main ones.</p>
<p>And about the serpent people, I have a few more ideas in mind.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;This&nbsp;is&nbsp;gonna&nbsp;be&nbsp;long&nbsp;so</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Spoilers</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>So my idea about the serpent people, is generally that they sort of established an empire maybe around Xia Dynasty or before that.</p>
<p>Despite being seen as serpent people, they aren't actually reptilians, but humans, manipulated their flesh so they resemble their divine parents, yeah. But instead of using Sarkic means, they kind of use machines to achieve that, they have a special machine that they will apply when they become adults (or maybe as soon as they're born, didn't decide on that yet), their genes and such stay human, but it is similar to Sarkic manipulation. But unlike Sarkic members, this change is permenant, and they don't further manipulate their apperance, and the machine can only be applied once. And despite worshipping the metal dragon, they don't seek to change themselves into machines either. They may have those if they are wounded or lost a limb, but they generally don't seek to intentionally make themselves machines. So it's less of a 50-50 balance between flesh and mechanical thing, but more of a they take a bit of both, but generally keeping from further manipulation. They're kind of satisified as they're made. (The heretical faction in modern times Foundation discovered however, does go with the 50-50 balance between flesh and mechanical thing, but they're still experimenting on those, not actually already achieving those.)</p>
<p>The serpent people, despite worshipping both gods, is more inclined to use the Mekhane technology. They kind of live longer than average humans, but they never really went the flesh manipulation direction too far. Basically, they use this programming language, Bagua, said to be the language of Fuxi, and builds all kind of machines, really high-tech side, and they even went to space. (They aslo kind of sealed the reap near Jupiter, but as their empire fall, nobody was sent to maintain the thing up there, so flesh is leaking :P) I imagine a small bunch of them went space expidition, and probably is still out there.</p>
<p>Their empire eventually falls after a war against another race (could be SCP-1000?) or it just falls as all empire does. As there is no empire to protect them anymore, the are kind of vulnerable to other people, who would of course see serpent people as something alien, and so they stopped using that machine that will alternate their flesh and give them serpent apperances. They later Chinese people bascially inherited their culture and some of their knowledge. I remember there are at least three skips with Terra-Cotta Warriors as robots, and even a spacecraft sent to space in Qin Dynasty, and in this headcanon, they're based on the remaining part of serpent-people tech. They serpent people aslo provoked the general dragon-serpent worship in China.</p>
<p>I aslo have the idea that, instead of being a ethnic group, Chinese, or Asian people would be oblivious to their existence. Generally, people in these region are all more or less descendants of the serpent poeple, and if apply the machine, they would become serpent people as well. And the bloodlines has such an effect that, anyone who is their descendants would fail to perceive them as abnormal. Meaning if a serpent person walks on the street, a foreigner would be scared and see that it's a snake man, but one with their bloodline would just think it's a man, despiting that he sees all the scales and serpent features. He would think it's completely normal unless pointed out, even them it would not induce any hateful reaction.</p>
<p>I've been meaning to write skips on these, but sadly never get to it. Hope I may be able to some day :P</p>
</div>
</div>
